task.summary:
Fixed alternate line inversion bug
TODO: effects not working on LED (bot fine in curses)

Commit before switching from bytearray to list.
led_buffer[256 int][3 bytes]
Two dimensional list in place. Bytearrays dropped, except for the final write to curses/LED display. All effects now applies to led_display list, but must be rewritten.
Implemented fader via RGB->VLS and VLS->RGB trickery to get access to "lightness".
Fixed problem with curses introduced by interrupt driven exit

Lots of small fixes
Timing fixes (a lot)
Zigzag layout now compensated (and threading bug fixed)
"speed" parameter for Scroller(...) now sane
Serial com made more robust (and overhead reduced)
A lot of code optimizations. Moved some functions out to SuperLED_lib Arduino code brushed up and rainbow() added Bug fixes Moved global variables to separate file (SuperLED_globals)
Smooth scrolling using anti-aliasing implemented (huge visual improvement for scrolling)
Cleaned up messy imports/global variables. Goal is to get rid of the globals, but for now the flags and buffers stay
A lot of bugs fixed (mostly to do with incomplete fixes from last commit)
